{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":7861,"name":"","username":"Enhex","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/enhex/{size}/81_2.png","created_at":"2015-09-16T16:22:49.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI‚Äôm trying to create a compound shape with SetCustomConvexHull().\u003cbr\u003e\nWhat happens is as if all the vertices are combined into a single mesh, and I get a single convex hull.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e// Create a collision shape for each shape, resulting compound collision\nfor (const auto\u0026amp; shape : shapes)\n{\n\t// Get the shape's geometry\n\tauto collisionGeometry = node-\u0026gt;CreateComponent\u0026lt;CustomGeometry\u0026gt;(LOCAL);\n\tfor (const auto\u0026amp; vertex : shape.vertices)\n\t{\n\t\tVector3 position(vertex.x, vertex.y, vertex.z);\n\t\tcollisionGeometry-\u0026gt;DefineVertex(position / scale);\n\t}\n\n\t// Create a collision shape\n\tauto collisionShape = node-\u0026gt;CreateComponent\u0026lt;CollisionShape\u0026gt;(LOCAL);\n\tcollisionShape-\u0026gt;SetCustomConvexHull(collisionGeometry);\n}\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf I use Set\u003ca\u003ePrimitive\u003c/a\u003e or SetConvexHull, it does work as expected, creating seperate shapes.\u003cbr\u003e\nIs it a bug with SetCustomConvexHull()?\u003cbr\u003e\nDoes a node can have only a single CustomGeometry component?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:07:16.309Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":17,"reads":15,"readers_count":14,"score":103.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":1372,"topic_slug":"cant-create-compound-collision-shapes-with-customgeometry","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":184,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":7862,"name":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","username":"cadaver","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/{size}/3_2.png","created_at":"2015-09-16T16:41:10.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThis is related to looking up the CustomGeometry in serialization. To have an unified mechanism for both immediate use and serialization, node ID‚Äôs are used. It ends up looking up the same (first) customgeometry for each shape, regardless of the pointer you give.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis should be changeble to use component ID‚Äôs instead.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:07:16.368Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":17,"readers_count":16,"score":3.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":1372,"topic_slug":"cant-create-compound-collision-shapes-with-customgeometry","display_username":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Urho3D Author","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":3,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":7863,"name":"","username":"Enhex","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/enhex/{size}/81_2.png","created_at":"2015-09-16T17:22:16.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eOk, I looked up what you said and saw it in the source code.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI want to use manually defined Urho3D::Model instead.\u003cbr\u003e\nI haven‚Äôt tried it yet, but when I looked in ConvexData::ConvexData I saw:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e        geom-\u0026gt;GetRawData(vertexData, vertexSize, indexData, indexSize, elementMask);\n        if (!vertexData || !indexData)\n        {\n            LOGWARNING(\"Skipping geometry with no CPU-side geometry data for convex hull collision\");\n            continue;\n        }\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf only vertexData is used, why would it skip if there‚Äôs no indexData?\u003cbr\u003e\nI want to get away with only defining a vertex buffer for a Model which is used exclusively for physics.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:07:16.452Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":15,"readers_count":14,"score":13.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":1372,"topic_slug":"cant-create-compound-collision-shapes-with-customgeometry","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":184,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":7864,"name":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","username":"cadaver","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/{size}/3_2.png","created_at":"2015-09-16T17:28:12.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eGood find, that‚Äôs just the result of copypaste and can be fixed.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePreferably we should be able to create VertexBuffers with no GPU side representation for these kinds of uses.\u003c/p\u003e","pos